    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-11T06:44:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-11T06:44:00-05:00" n="500"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d500">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.7961/4: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-11T11:00:00-00:44"
                            >May 11, 1942—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 3:07 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>147. My British colleague states he has been instructed to request of Liberian
                    Government, general permission for British aircraft flying between British West
                    African territories to land on Liberian territory for purpose of refueling, if
                    and when circumstances require. He has approached me to ascertain if I see any
                    reason why such request should not be made. I have informed him I can see no
                    reason, but have asked him to wait until I received Department’s views on matter
                    before making his request. A reply to this telegram is therefore urgently
                    requested.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wharton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
